						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Fellowships-grants-calls/CIMMYT-Wheat-Improvement-Positions" title="CIMMYT: Wheat Improvement Positions" alt="link">CIMMYT: Wheat Improvement Positions</a></h2>

	
					<p>
The International Maize and Wheat Improvement Center (CIMMYT) is seeking two suitable qualified candidates for positions as
Wheat Improvement Scientist and Postdoctoral Fellow (Wheat Breeding/Agronomy) in support of its global development of improved
wheat for developing countries. The positions offer an outstanding career opportunity for scientists interested in global wheat research
and breeding and will be based in Kabul, Afghanistan. The successful candidates will facilitate the introduction and evaluation of global
wheat germplasm for Afghanistan and contribute to the development of improved cultivars and crop management practices in close
collaboration with colleagues in the CIMMYT Global Wheat Program, and national scientists in the Agricultural Research Institute ofAfghanistan. The appointment is initially for three (3) years, with opportunity for extension into a career position. Deadline: <b>31 July 2009</b></p>
							<p><span class="date">23/07/2009</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Fellowships-grants-calls/CIMMYT-Wheat-Improvement-Positions">Read more...</a>
